Execute only PHASE 08.2.

Goal:
Add JWT authentication, refresh tokens, password hashing, RBAC, auth dependencies, and route protection without breaking dev-mode usability.

Create or update:
backend/app/auth/__init__.py
backend/app/auth/models.py
backend/app/auth/password.py
backend/app/auth/jwt.py
backend/app/auth/rbac.py
backend/app/auth/dependencies.py
backend/app/auth/auth_service.py
backend/app/api/auth.py
backend/app/main.py
backend/app/core/config.py
backend/app/api/*.py where protection is needed
backend/app/tests/test_auth_service.py
backend/app/tests/test_auth_api.py
backend/app/tests/test_rbac.py

Auth endpoints:
POST /api/auth/login
POST /api/auth/refresh
POST /api/auth/logout
GET  /api/auth/me
POST /api/auth/bootstrap-admin

Roles:
- admin
- operator
- analyst
- viewer

Permissions:
admin:
- all permissions

operator:
- read dashboard
- run dry-run trading
- manage scheduler
- manage content approval
- run backtests
- control dry-run IoT
- halt/resume risk system

analyst:
- read dashboard
- run backtests
- read logs
- read risk
- read trading signals

viewer:
- read dashboard only

Public:
- GET /health
- POST /api/auth/login
- POST /api/auth/refresh

Authenticated:
- GET /api/agents
- GET /api/logs
- dashboard read APIs

Permission protected:
- POST /api/risk/halt
- POST /api/risk/resume
- POST /api/scheduler/jobs
- POST /api/scheduler/jobs/{id}/run
- DELETE /api/scheduler/jobs/{id}
- POST /api/iot/action
- POST /api/iot/power-cycle
- POST /api/content/approve
- POST /api/content/post
- POST /api/backtesting/results/{id}/promotion-check

Rules:
- Never return password hashes.
- Never log passwords or tokens.
- Bootstrap admin only if no users exist.
- Bootstrap admin disabled in production unless explicitly allowed.
- Dev mode may allow dashboard without auth if AUTH_ENABLED=false.
- Production must reject default JWT_SECRET_KEY.
- Production must reject default admin password.

Validation:
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m ruff check app tests
python -B -m pytest -q

